<div data-role="page" id="ref_prep_frame-actions">
	<div data-role="header" data-add-back-btn="true" data-position="fixed" data-tap-toggle="false">
		<h1>Frame Actions</h1>
	</div>
	<div role="main" class="ui-content">
		<p>Each frame begins its turn by determining the dicepool it will use. A player assigns dice from this pool in order to take action. Every frame starts with 2 white dice. These represent the frame itself and its pilot. Every frame has four actions it is capable of taking. The baseline actions that any frame may take are:</p>

		<ul>
			<li>Defend</li>
			<li>Move (navigating around cover)</li>
			<li>Attack at hand-to-hand range</li>
			<li>Spot a target which is out of cover and within direct-fire or hand-to-hand range</li>
		</ul>

		<p>A frame&#8217;s capabilites may be extended by various methods (systems, single-shot rockets, and sprinting) which provide additional dice to the pool. In each case, these extensions are restricted to being assigned to specific actions.</p>

		<p>Each action can be taken once per turn. A player may not have enough dice in the pool to take all four actions and will need to choose which to perform.</p>
	</div>
</div>
